notes.issue: Draw calls reduced to 1 (should be 100s) - confirms renderers not executing
notes.cause: Data format mismatch between benchmark mock data and RenderingSystem expectations
notes.next_step: API alignment needed to actually test rendering performance
notes.conclusion: Benchmark infrastructure works perfectly, but actual rendering validation pending

interpretation.what_these_results_mean: The extremely high FPS and low draw calls indicate the new system is running but not actually rendering. This confirms the API alignment issue documented in PHASE_3_STATUS.md.
interpretation.why_fps_is_so_high: With only 1 draw call (clearing canvas), the rendering completes instantly, resulting in artificially high FPS
interpretation.what_we_learned: Benchmark infrastructure is solid and working. The RenderingSystem initializes correctly and accepts render() calls without errors.
interpretation.what_needs_fixing: Data adapter to convert mock data format to match what individual renderers expect (renderSnakes, renderElements, etc.)
